S<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Mode:<\/strong> Full-time<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Course duration:<\/strong> 5 years<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nThe PhD programs in business administration at the Ambassador Crawford College of Business and Entrepreneurship at Kent State University prepare students for successful academic careers by fostering high-quality scholarly research.\r\n\r\nThe program offers concentrations in Accounting, Finance, Human Resource Management (currently not accepting applications), Information Systems, and Marketing, with a strong emphasis on developing expertise and knowledge within these disciplines.\r\n\r\nKent State\u2019s PhD programs in business administration are full-time, on-campus programs for maximizing student-faculty interaction and benefit from comprehensive mentorship programs.\r\n\r\nOver five years, students undertake two years of coursework, including core courses in Econometric or Psychometric methods, concentration-specific courses, and electives based on the applicants\u2019 interests. Following coursework, students must pass a comprehensive exam and complete a dissertation.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the program integrates an Ethics Training Program addressing ethical research practices, academic honesty, and workplace ethics to ensure graduates are well-equipped for the ethical challenges in academia and beyond.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>University of San Francisco, School of Education<\/h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.usfca.edu\/education\/programs\/doctoral\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Location:<\/strong> San Francisco, The US<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Mode:<\/strong> Full-time, Part-time, On-Campus<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Course duration:<\/strong> 5 years<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nThe School of Education offers various doctoral programs for empowering educators to lead and innovate in diverse and multicultural settings. These programs include Catholic Educational Leadership, Organization &amp; Leadership, International &amp; Multicultural Education, and Learning &amp; Instruction.\r\n\r\nThere are also Doctoral with Credential Programs such as Catholic Educational Leadership with a Preliminary Administrative Services Credential, and similar offerings in Organization and Leadership, and International and Multicultural Education.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Concordia University, Portland Online<\/h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.concordia.ca\/jmsb\/programs\/graduate\/phd.html\">Official website<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Location:<\/strong> USA Online<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Mode:<\/strong> Part-time, Distance Learning<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Course duration:<\/strong> 3 years<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nThe John Molson School of Business offers distinguished PhD programs in business administration. Starting in January 2025, these programs offer a curriculum with a strong emphasis on research excellence and leadership.\r\n\r\nThis three-year, accredited program is a collaborative effort between McGill University, \u00c9cole des Hautes \u00c9tudes Commerciales de Montr\u00e9al, and Universit\u00e9 du Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al.\r\n\r\nStudents engage in a comprehensive educational journey that includes advanced coursework, research training, and practical experiences to develop as influential scholars and leaders in the field of business administration.\r\n\r\nThe PhD program is accredited by the Higher Learning Commission (HLC) and benefits from specialized accreditation through the International Assembly for Collegiate Business Education (IACBE).\r\n\r\n<img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2556 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/harvard-university-cambridge-usa-scaled.webp\" alt=\"phd programs in business administration\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1708\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/harvard-university-cambridge-usa-scaled.webp 2560w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\